options.description:
True, we can find the size of short integer and long integer using the sizeof() operator. Example:


#include<stdio.h>
int main()
{
    short int i = 10;
    long int j = 10;
    printf("short int is %d bytes.,\nlong int is %d bytes.",
            sizeof(i),sizeof(j));
    return 0;
}


Output:
short int is 2 bytes.
long int is 4 bytes.
